HEADWORD: Pirn
<hw>Pirn</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Etymol.
uncertain.]</ety> <def>A quill or reed on which thread or yarn is wound;
a bobbin; also, the wound yarn on a weaver's shuttle; also, the reel of
a fishing rod.</def> <mark>[Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pirogue</ent>⟦br⟧
